Male: head, frontal view (A); habitus, dorsal view (B); habitus, lateral view (C).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,873,1619]" pageId="4" pageNumber="321">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,330,873,899]" pageId="4" pageNumber="321">Terminalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[347,418,873,900]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1506,1530]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1107,1481]" captionTargetId="figure-309@6.[151,1435,1107,1482]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Botanophila mayorgae sp. nov. Male terminalia: (A) sternite 5, dorsal view; (B) epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; (C) epandrium, cerci and surstyli, lateral view; (D) aedeagus and associated structures, lateral view; (E) aedeagus and associated structures, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cerc, cerci; distph, distiphallus; epand, epandrium; epiph, epiphallus; phapod, phalapodeme; pgt, postgonite; pregt, pregonite; sur, surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141829/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="321">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
): Cerci in posterior view, enlarged and long, twice longer than its width, shorter than the surstyli, apically furcated, with an acute point on each side and among them a median apical process (
<figureCitation box="[1281,1369,909,936]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1506,1530]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1107,1481]" captionTargetId="figure-309@6.[151,1435,1107,1482]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Botanophila mayorgae sp. nov. Male terminalia: (A) sternite 5, dorsal view; (B) epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; (C) epandrium, cerci and surstyli, lateral view; (D) aedeagus and associated structures, lateral view; (E) aedeagus and associated structures, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cerc, cerci; distph, distiphallus; epand, epandrium; epiph, epiphallus; phapod, phalapodeme; pgt, postgonite; pregt, pregonite; sur, surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141829/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="321">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
). Surstyli long, narrow, and slightly curved. Hypopygium (
<figureCitation box="[763,888,945,972]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1506,1530]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1107,1481]" captionTargetId="figure-309@6.[151,1435,1107,1482]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Botanophila mayorgae sp. nov. Male terminalia: (A) sternite 5, dorsal view; (B) epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; (C) epandrium, cerci and surstyli, lateral view; (D) aedeagus and associated structures, lateral view; (E) aedeagus and associated structures, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cerc, cerci; distph, distiphallus; epand, epandrium; epiph, epiphallus; phapod, phalapodeme; pgt, postgonite; pregt, pregonite; sur, surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141829/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="321">Figs 5D, E</figureCitation>
) of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lioy" authorityYear="1864" box="[980,1118,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Botanophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[980,1118,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="321">Botanophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- 
<typeStatus box="[1126,1178,946,972]" pageId="4" pageNumber="321">type</typeStatus>
, i.e. pregonite reduced and shallow, firmly connected to the central plate of hypandrium, and with 2 long setae; postgonite twice longer than pregonite; epiphallus and distiphallus reduced; distiphallus largely membranous except for a pair of anterobasal sclerotized rods (
<figureCitation box="[413,537,1053,1080]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1506,1530]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1107,1481]" captionTargetId="figure-309@6.[151,1435,1107,1482]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Botanophila mayorgae sp. nov. Male terminalia: (A) sternite 5, dorsal view; (B) epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; (C) epandrium, cerci and surstyli, lateral view; (D) aedeagus and associated structures, lateral view; (E) aedeagus and associated structures, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cerc, cerci; distph, distiphallus; epand, epandrium; epiph, epiphallus; phapod, phalapodeme; pgt, postgonite; pregt, pregonite; sur, surstyli." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141829/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="321">Fig. 5D, E</figureCitation>
); phallapodema long and apically enlarged in dorsal (
